  "prompt": "How do I remove another Google account from my Android?",
  "response": "To remove another Google account from your Android device, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Open Settings**: Navigate to the \"Settings\" app on your device.\n\n2. **Accounts**: Scroll down and tap on \"Accounts\" or \"Users & accounts,\" depending on your device.\n\n3. **Select Google**: Tap on \"Google\" from the list of account types.\n\n4. **Choose Account**: You will see a list of Google accounts linked to your device. Tap on the account you want to remove.\n\n5. **Remove Account**: Tap on the three vertical dots (\u22ee) in the top right corner, then select \"Remove account.\"\n\n6. **Confirm**: Confirm the action by tapping \"Remove account\" again in the dialog box that appears.\n\nThis will disconnect the selected Google account from your Android device. Note that removing the account will also remove all associated data, such as contacts, emails, and synced app data, from your device.",
